value: Breeds locally in southeastern Russia and in Siberia from the lower Ural River, the Tobol, the mouths of the Yana, Indigirka and Kolyma rivers south to Turgai, the upper Ob, northern Turkestan, Transbaikalia and Ussuriland. Winters in northwestern India and in China.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Breeds Arctic Siberia; winters to n India and China

breeding grounds are wet sedge/cotton-grass marshes, moss swamps and damp shores of lakes, mainly in typical subarctic tundra, and scrub tundra, to a lesser extent in wooded tundra and the northern taiga;world population late 1990s= ca.2500 birds
